<TITLE> Schools to have double shift from Jan </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 7 (bdnews24.com)  The government is introducing double shift in 80 government secondary schools of 41 districts across the country from January to cope with the increased number of students, the education minister said on Monday. "We are taking the initiative to deal with the additional pressure of students and create scope for students to enroll in good educational institutions," Nurul Islam Nahid told reporters at the Secretariat. About 2,000 additional teachers will be appointed soon for running the shifts, he said. The minister said the primary and secondary schools will start their next session from Jan 2 so that students can complete their syllabus in time. "To make the admission process transparent we have made arrangements for uniform admission form of 317 government schools." The private schools have been asked to follow the same procedure, Nahid said. He said the government has already sent all the Madrassa level textbooks and 80 percent textbooks to the secondary schools. He hoped the remaining books will be sent before Jan 2. Nahid said the government has identified 30 Madrassas as a model for modernisation of Madarassa curriculum. These Madarassas will be provided with new buildings and modern laboratories at the cost of Tk 9.0 million, he added. b
